<br>
Here's a very samuraiesque style that appeals to me/<br>
<br>
Deathblow<br>
<br>
Preq: Weapons must be sheathed.<br>
Timer: 5min<br>
Effect: When you hit this your weapons draw and you hit with an instant swipe that does about 4 or 5times normal damage as a regular blow maybe more.<br>
<br>
To me this would be very useful in those first few painful seconds of caster and healer killing and will deal with that enchater pbaoe;ing you in a hurry.<br>
<br>
Rock Throw<br>
<br>
Preq: weapons must be sheathed(cant throw rocks with hands occupied)<br>
Timer: 3min<br>
Effect low damage insta that works at about half a bolts range that stops castin for ten seconds.<br>
<br>
Now this is rogueish. We can throw mud why not rocks? This helps the hardest part of being an offensive tank, getting to the caster or mezzer to even do soemthing about him/her.<br>
<br>
Kick Off<br>
<br>
Timer 5min<br>
<br>
Effect: low damage and pushes target back 5-10 paces stuns for four.<br>
<br>
Another rogueish kind of ability.  Big warrior givin ya problems as you beat down the skald? kick him away.  Though i think resists can be put into affect for guys who carry a shield or have a much higher strength. i.e.: Kicking the troll with a saracean was a bad idea.<br>
<br>
ill come up with more later as i think about em. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=esfblueriver>esfblueriver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#000000>(7/6/03 4:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=268.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Unique RA</span><hr size=1> Dirty Fighting<br>
Type of Feat: General<br>
The character knows brutal and effective fighting tactics. By sacrificing all other attacks during a round, the character can eleft to perform a dirty fighting move that will deal an extra 1d4 points of damage.<br>
<br>
er.....<br>
<br>
Dirty Fighting - 10 RA points - 30 second duration - 7 minute cooldown<br>
<br>
The character takes an attack speed decrease in order to deal more devistating attacks. Effect: 35% atk speed debuff, for 35% DPS increase.  Note this change takes effect before style dps bonuses are calculated, so the actual damage done by styles would also increase. Dirty Tricks cannot be activated at the same time.<br>
<br>
