10 ra points- Every 100 rp's the merc accumulates, he gains 1 gold. We're mercenaries. Paid soldiers. We should be paid somehow.<br>
<br>
Ability 2- Low Blow<br>
5 ra points- The opponent is kicked (punched if inconnu) where the sun don't shine. They cannot attack for 9 seconds, but can move at a slightly slowed rate (maybe 80% snare). Ability cannot be purged...have you ever been kicked in the crotch? Yeah. You can't just &quot;purge&quot; that kinda thing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Ability 3- Unhonorable combat<br>
3 Ra points: Merc recieves (medium for 3 Ra points..maybe push up to 6 or 10 to add much larger damage) damage bonuses to positional (unhonorable) attacks. This goes well with both the merc concept of fighting dirty and the light tank concept as a whole. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#000000>(7/7/03 11:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=268.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RAs</span><hr size=1> &lt;laughs real hard&gt;<br>
